Egg Roll Tacos
  --Brandon, Pinch of Yum

Tacos:
1 lb ground chicken, turkey, or pork
3 tbsp shoyu
1 tbsp chili crisp
1 tbsp garlic paste (or 2 cloves garlic, grated)
1 tbsp ginger paste (or a 1/2" piece ginger, grated)
1 c shredded cabbage and carrots mix (great time to use a store-bought coleslaw or salad mix, where the base is cabbage)
6–8 small flour tortillas (eg Mission Street Taco)
2–3 tbsp avocado oil or toasted sesame oil

Mix the ground meat, shoyu, chili crisp, garlic, ginger, and veggies together. Press the mixture onto one side of the tortillas. It's easiest to do all of them at once, before you start cooking them. Heat a skillet over medium high heat. Add the oil. Working in batches, add the tacos, meat-side down, and cook for 3-4 min until they are browned. Flip to the back side for 1 min to get the tortillas a bit golden, and then finish with one more flip to being meat-side down to ensure it’s cooked through. (165F for chicken and turkey, 160F for ground pork.)

Toppings:
More fresh cabbage / carrot mix (can use the same bag from before!)
Fresh cilantro or green onion
Chili crisp
Gochujang sauce

Top with more fresh cabbage, cilantro or green onions, and your sauces of choice. Fold in half – it eats kind of like a hybrid between a taco and sandwich, but tastes like an eggroll. 
